		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If you delay frames by the repeating pattern 16, 17, 17, 16, 17, 17 ...  then the average is exactly 16.666666... msec between frames. Moral of the story: regardless of timing granularity, you can <em>on average</em> get a delay to any precision you like. You could have the average delay be exactly 16.1234567 msec, even though you can only delay by whole milliseconds.</div>
<br />
<br />It worked for Allegro. Well, now I get exactly 60FPS, thanks a lot, since it was a very very old issue.
<br />
<br />About the sound, I'm still having problems with sync... but I'm thinking &amp; trying different things...

		

